    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Botschantzevia karatavica are antioxidant, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, these compounds neutralizing free radicals and preventing oxidative stress. The plant also exhibits antimicrobial properties, inhibiting the growth of bacteria and fungi through the action of volatile oils and saponins, thus providing protection against infections. Additionally, Botschantzevia karatavica has anti-inflammatory properties, reducing swelling and pain by suppressing the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, mediated by bioactive compounds such as sesquiterpenes and triterpenoids. Furthermore, the plant shows analgesic properties, alleviating pain by modulating the activity of pain-sensing neurons in the central nervous system, which is associated with the presence of alkaloids and glycosides. Its antifungal properties, meanwhile, are attributed to the action of terpenes and phenolic compounds, which inhibit the growth of fungi and prevent the development of fungal infections.",
